                        <p>To solve <m>\frac{x-<var name="$e"/>}{<var name="$b"/>}=-\frac{<var name="$c"/>}{<var name="$d"/>}</m> for <m>x</m>, we can multiply both sides of the equation by <m><var name="$b"/></m>, then simplify the right side of the equation, and then subtract <m><var name="$e"/></m>. <md>
                            <mrow>\frac{x-<var name="$e"/>}{<var name="$b"/>} \multiplyright{<var name="$b"/>}\amp= -\frac{<var name="$c"/>}{<var name="$d"/>} \multiplyright{<var name="$b"/>} </mrow>

                            <mrow>x-<var name="$e"/> \amp= -\frac{<var name="$c"/> \cdot <var name="$b"/>}{<var name="$d"/>}</mrow>
                            
                            <mrow>x-<var name="$e"/> + <var name="$e"/> \amp= -<var name="$cbd"/>+ <var name="$e"/></mrow>

                            <mrow> x \amp= <var name="$Ans"/></mrow>
                        </md></p>
                        <p>Since <m>\frac{<var name="$Ans"/>-<var name="$e"/>}{<var name="$b"/>}</m> and <m>-\frac{<var name="$c"/>}{<var name="$d"/>}</m> both are equivalent to <m><var name="$r"/></m>, <m> <var name="$Ans"/> </m> is verified as the solution and the solution set is <m>\left\{ <var name="$Ans"/> \right\}</m>.</p>
                    </solution>
                </webwork>
