                    </setup>
                    <statement>
                        <p>To try to determine the health of the Rocky Mountain elk population in the Wenaha Wildlife Area, the Oregon Department of Fish and Wildlife caught, tagged, and released <m><var name="$tt" /></m> Rocky Mountain elk.  A week later, they returned and observed <m><var name="$sp" /></m> Rocky Mountain elk, <m><var name="$st" /></m> of which had tags.  Approximately how many Rocky Mountain elk are in the Wenaha Wildlife Area?</p>
                        <p>There are approximately <var name="$Ans" width="10" /> elk in the wildlife area.</p>
                    </statement>
                    <solution>
                        <p>Let <m>x</m> represent how many elk are in the Wenaha Wildlife Area.</p>
                        <p>To solve this use a proportion, we begin by setting up a ratio from the sample where we know all the values: <m>\frac{<var name="$st" /> \text{ tagged elk}}{<var name="$sp"/>\text{ total elk}}</m></p>
                        <p>We then set up a second ratio, using the same structure, where one value is unknown: <m>\frac{<var name="$tt" /> \text{ tagged elk}}{x \text{ total elk}}</m> </p>
                        <p>We finish by setting the two ratios equal and solve the resulting proportion. <md>
                            <mrow>\frac{<var name="$st" />}{<var name="$sp"/>} \amp= \frac{<var name="$tt"/>}{x}</mrow>
                            <mrow>\frac{<var name="$st" />}{<var name="$sp"/>} \multiplyright{<var name="$sp"/>\cdot x} \amp= \frac{<var name="$tt"/>}{x}\multiplyright{<var name="$sp"/>\cdot x}</mrow>
                            <mrow><var name="$st" /> \cdot x \amp= <var name="$tt"/>\cdot <var name="$sp"/></mrow>
                            <mrow>\divideunder{<var name="$st" /> \cdot x}{<var name="$st" />} \amp= \divideunder{<var name="$tt"/>\cdot <var name="$sp"/>}{<var name="$st" />}</mrow>
                            <mrow>x \amp= <var name="$Ans"/></mrow>
                        </md>There are approximately <m><var name="$Ans"/></m> elk in the Wenaha Wildlife Area.  </p>
                    </solution>
